body:
Actually the above should be clear:

..when retrieving pending transactions, logs or blocks. So example request could be:
- eth_getBlockByNumber (when using parameter ["pending"])

```
{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"eth_getBlockByNumber","params":["pending",false],"id":3}
```
- eth_getTransactionByHash (provide a hash of a pending transaction, e.g. create one immedieately before with sendTransaction)

```
{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"eth_sendTransaction","params":[{"from":"0x1233","to":"0x1234","value":"0xb"}],"id":5}

{jsonrpc: "2.0", method: "eth_getTransactionByHash", params: ["0x1234"], id: 6}
```
- eth_getFilterChanges (created with eth_newFilter and eth_newPendingTransactionFilter)

```
{jsonrpc: "2.0", method: "eth_newPendingTransactionFilter", params: [], id: 6}
{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"eth_getFilterChanges","params":["0x0"],"id":10}

// or
{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"eth_newFilter","params":[{"topics":[],"fromBlock":"0x0","toBlock":"pending"}],"id":87}
{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"eth_getFilterChanges","params":["0x1"],"id":10}
```
- eth_getFilterLogs (created with eth_newPendingTransactionFilter) (not sure, if that should work, as pending transactions are always recent, its currently undefined)

For all the above you obviously need to fill in the correct properties (e.g. you from address) and return values in the following calls.
